<br>
For me, EverQuest was just about the only social outlet I had while I was cooped up at home for almost a year with Hodgkin's Lymphoma (a lymphatic cancer).  My immune system was severly depressed due to the disease and the chemotherapy being used to treat it, and as such, I could not go out for the most part, and could only have limited contact with people at all, IF my white blood count had been good at the last blood test (which was at least once a week, if not more)  <br>
<br>
Another interesting point is that I met my current boyfriend through EverQuest.  A casual acquaintance at first, then joined my guild, we got to talking, met in person and really hit it off...<br>
<br>
Oh, and I hardly play EQ anymore...work and having to get stuff done around the house makes it so I have limited hours to try to get my 59th level rogue to 60th.<br>
<br>
So, take that, lady...some of us are "normal", your son was not! <p><center>
